# 6. ストリートのセカイ

Kohane: A-An event?!
Akito: Yeah. Now that you're a group, why not? We should perform together as artists who have a shared vision.
Akito: There's an event we're part of next month that had one of their performers back out, so they've got an empty slot to fill.
Akito: It's at a live house called RED. What do you think?
Toya: .....
An: RED, huh? It's kinda on the small side, so it might be good for a first performance.
An: What do you think, Kohane? It's a good opportunity, and I can't wait for people to hear us sing!
Kohane: B-But next month is so soon... Will I be all right...?
An: You'll be fine! If it's next month, we'll have plenty of time to practice. Besides, I'll be right there with you.
Kohane: (Oh, that's right. If we're singing together, that means I won't be up there by myself.)
Kohane: I think...I can handle that...
Akito: It's settled, then. I'll let them know you'll be there.
An: Okay! Thanks for the invite, Akito.
Akito: Don't mention it. This'll be our first time performing at the same event. I'm looking forward to it.
Toya: .....
Toya: What was that all about, Akito? Why did you invite them out of the blue like that?
Akito: Did you know I played soccer until I started junior high?
Toya: Hm?
Akito: Before I knew it, my skill made me the best on the team. And even though I was never really into it, the expectations of those around me made me think I wanted to go pro.
Akito: But I realized something the first time I went up against a nationally ranked team. Those who have their eye on a goal are on a completely different level.
Akito: Whether it's free time, eating, or even sleep, those kinds of people will sacrifice everything to work toward their goal.
Toya: .....
Akito: Seeing RAD WEEKEND was the first time I felt like I'd found something I could sacrifice everything for.
Akito: I always thought Shiraishi was the same way. After all, she was there too.
Akito: I'd hoped she was different than all the others who like to talk big, and that she really wanted to surpass RAD WEEKEND.
Akito: But now she's gone and teamed up with a complete amateur.
Akito: There's no way she can surpass that night teamed up with some timid, half-hearted noob like that.
Toya: .....
Akito: So I'm going to teach her a lesson. We'll overwhelm them with our performance, and make sure they realize that they don't have what it takes.
Toya: ...Akito, don't you think it's a bit early to assume they're only doing this half-heartedly?
Akito: Were you even paying attention to that kid?
Akito: She said she's only ever sang during music class. Someone like her doesn't even have the right to use RAD WEEKEND's name.
Akito: Saying you're going to surpass that night...
An's Father: ♪ ——! ——! ——!
Akito: Isn't something you can say half-heartedly.
Akito: And that is why we'll crush them with our singing.
Toya: .....
An: Now that we've decided to be part of an event, we should figure out what we're going to sing.
Kohane: Yeah, you're right.
Kohane & An: ♪——!
An: That was great! And it looks like you can handle the more difficult songs without any problem. You really are amazing, Kohane.
Kohane: N-No, I'm...
An: That's probably good for a list of possible choices. Are there any other songs you can think of?
Kohane: Um, what do you think about this song done by Miku?
An: Oh, this one's really cool! Sure, let's add it to the list.
Kohane: Okay! Huh?
An: What's up?
Kohane: There's a song in the playlist that doesn't have a title.
An: Huh? Hey, you're right. It just says Untitled.
An: I bet there was a problem with the download or something. Try playing it to see which one it is.
Kohane: Okay. Huh? I don't hear anything. I guess it must not have downloaded all the way.
An: Kohane... Is it just me or is your phone glowing?
Kohane: Is it? You're right. The title is starting to— ah! I can't see!
Kohane: Wh-Whoa, that scared me. W-What just happened?
Kohane: ...!! Um, wh-where are we?
An: I don't recognize this street. We were just in the cafe, weren't we? How did we get outside?
Kohane: I know, we can check the map on my phone. Huh? I-It's not working... Wh-What's going on?
An: Hm... Why don't we take a look around? Maybe we'll find a familiar street.
Kohane: O-Okay. I don't recognize this place, but somehow I still get the feeling I've seen it before.
An: You too? I get the same feeling. It kind of reminds me of Vivid Street.
An: Look! This is a RAD WEEKEND flyer!
An: What's it doing here? Dad said they all disappeared after the event.
Kohane: Hey, An! There's a shop over there!
An: Oh, you're right. It looks like a cafe. Let's go ask them for directions.
An: Excuse me! Is there anyone here?
???: Welcome. Oh, there you are. You've finally come to visit.
Kohane: M-Miku?!
